  i innerText is not recommended for reading DOM node text.
  
    1 │ /* should generate diagnostics */
  > 2 │ const text = node.innerText;
      │                   ^^^^^^^^^
    3 │ const computed = node["innerText"];
    4 │ const maybe = node?.innerText;
  
  i innerText depends on rendered layout and CSS, so it can be slower and produce different results from the DOM tree's text content.
  
  i Use textContent when you want the node's text without rendered-text behavior.
  
  i This rule belongs to the nursery group, which means it is not yet stable and may change in the future. Visit https://biomejs.dev/linter/#nursery for more information.
  
  i Unsafe fix: Use textContent instead.
  
